wikipedia_page.main: Frances Parthenope Verney, Lady Verney (née Nightingale; 19 April 1819 - 12 May 1890), was an English writer and journalist.

response: * Frances Parthenope Verney, Parthenope Nightingale, the elder sister of Florence Nightingale and wife of Sir Harry Verney, named after her place of birth in Naples
* Frances Parthenope Verney, nee Nightingale (1819–1890), British novelist, economist, social commentator, and journalist.
